    "created_at": "2015-01-12T19:25:33Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-01-12T19:25:33Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "It was a fairly pathological circumstance caused by attempting to completely isolate an application from its environment. I have worked around it trivially by adding /usr/bin to the path so that `which` exists. I am fine with this being marked wont-fix or just closed, it's a fairly weird maybe-bug that very few people will experience. I just figured that since I ran into it and was surprised I should probably report it and let you decide what you want to do with it :)\n"
  },
