    "updated_at": "2015-01-15T00:54:23Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think the biggest difference is that our `find_cmd` on Windows will look for things with a .py extension (e.g. `find_cmd('foo')` will match foo.py), whereas shutil.which() won't unless you add .py to the PATHEXT envvar.\n\nProbably easiest to leave it alone for now, but I might look into replacing it at some point.\n"
